nd country. If you are looking to escape the mind-numbing crowd of the high powered city life, then availing a Sri Lanka tour package from the Namaste India Trip will give you the much-needed peace and relaxation you need. Plunge into the island laced with ancient history and modern marvels that co-exist peacefully with each other. Travelers opt for a trip to Sri Lanka in search of deep serenity, unparalleled tranquility and as an option for being one of the most fun-packed offbeat destinations in the world.<\/p>\n<p>The entire island is riddled with prehistoric wonders and traces of Portuguese, British and Dutch settlements which till present day has been well preserved and attracts visitors from across the globe. Sri Lanka is one place which is easy to reach (hassle-free visa availability), made for family visitations and leaves a mark on every traveler\u2019s memory.<\/p>\n<h2 style=\"color:#1a0dab;text-decoration:none;margin-bottom:10px\">FAQs for Sri Lanka Tour Packages<\/h2>\n<h4>Q1: How Much Does Sri Lanka Trip Cost?<\/h4>\n<p>A. The cost of a Sri Lanka trip varies depending on factors such as duration, accommodation level, and inclusions. On average, a budget-friendly trip might start at around \u20b9 66,477, while a more luxurious experience could range from \u20b9 1,24,650 to \u20b9 2,49,301 or more per person, excluding flights.<\/p>\n<h4>Q2: How Many Days Is Enough In Sri Lanka?<\/h4>\n<p>A. To experience Sri Lanka highlights, a 10 to 14-day itinerary is recommended. This duration allows you to explore cultural sites like Sigiriya and Dambulla, enjoy coastal beauty in Mirissa or Trincomalee, and immerse in the lush landscapes of Ella and Nuwara Eliya, ensuring a well-rounded and memorable journey.<\/p>\n<h4>Q3: What Is The Best Month To Visit Sri Lanka?<\/h4>\n<p>A. The ideal time to visit Sri Lanka is during its dry seasons. For the west and south coasts, December to March offers pleasant weather, while the east coast is best visited from May to September. These months provide optimal conditions for sightseeing, outdoor activities, and enjoying the beaches.<\/p>\n<h4>Q4: How Can I Go To Sri Lanka From India?<\/h4>\n<p>A. Traveling from India to Sri Lanka is convenient. Direct flights are available from major Indian cities like Chennai, Mumbai, Delhi, and Bangalore to Sri Lanka's international airports in Colombo and Mattala. Flight durations are typically around 1.5 to 3 hours, making it a quick and accessible journey.<\/p>\n<h4>Q5: Are 7 Days Enough For Sri Lanka?<\/h4>\n<p>A. A 7-day trip to Sri Lanka offers a glimpse of its beauty. You can explore highlights like Colombo, Kandy, Sigiriya, and Galle. While it's a relatively short visit, careful planning lets you experience cultural richness, scenic landscapes, and historical sites, making the most of your time in this vibrant destination.<\/p>\n<\/p><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"cmsmasters_row_673c2d63a2b2a0_80085066\" class=\"cmsmasters_row cmsmasters_color_scheme_default cmsmasters_row_top_default cmsmasters_row_bot_default cmsmasters_row_boxed\">\n<div id=\"tx3\" class=\"cmsmasters_row_outer_parent\">\n<div class=\"cmsmasters_row_outer\">\n<div class=\"cmsmasters_row_inner\">\n<div class=\"cmsmasters_row_margin\">\n<div class=\"cmsmasters_column one_fourth\">\n<div class=\"custom_html\">\n<div class=\"xLeft\">\n<h3>Speciality Tour<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li><input type=\"checkbox\" value=\"all\" id=\"holiday\"><label for=\"holiday\">Customized Holidays<\/label><\/li>\n<li><input type=\"checkbox\" value=\"all\" id=\"family\"><label for=\"family\">Family<\/label><\/li>\n<li><input type=\"checkbox\" value=\"all\" id=\"women\"><label for=\"women\">Women's Special<\/label><\/li>\n<li><input type=\"checkbox\" value=\"all\" id=\"honeymoon\"><label for=\"honeymoon\">Honeymoon Special<\/label><\/li>\n<li><input type=\"checkbox\" value=\"all\" id=\"seniors\"><label for=\"seniors\">Seniors' Special<\/label><\/li>\n<li><